  "prompt": "Is Keynote better than Power Point?",
  "response": "The choice between Keynote and PowerPoint depends on individual needs and preferences. Here are some comparisons:\n\nKeynote (Apple):\n- More visually appealing and modern design\n- Easier to use for Mac and iOS users\n- Smoother animations and transitions\n- Better integration with Apple ecosystem\n- Free for Apple device owners\n- Simpler interface\n\nPowerPoint (Microsoft):\n- More widely used in business and professional settings\n- Greater compatibility across different devices and platforms\n- More advanced features and customization options\n- Better collaboration tools\n- More comprehensive design and formatting options\n- Part of Microsoft Office suite\n\nPros of Keynote:\n- Sleek design\n- User-friendly\n- High-quality graphics\n- Free for Apple users\n\nPros of PowerPoint:\n- More universal\n- More feature-rich\n- Better for complex presentations\n- Works on more devices\n\nThe best choice depends on:\n- Your device (Mac vs. Windows)\n- Your professional needs\n- Personal preference\n- Audience and presentation context\n\nIf you're primarily in the Apple ecosystem, Keynote might be better. For broader compatibility and more features, PowerPoint is typically recommended.",
